    <fr:title text="synthetic quasicoherence in the object classifier">synthetic quasicoherence in the object classifier</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be the generic object in the object classifier <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Set}{\mathopen {}\left  [V\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Then the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V+1\to  V^V]]></fr:tex> mapping <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {inl}\,x]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda \_.x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {inr}\,{\mathopen {}\left (\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  x.x]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-008V/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-008V/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="synthetic quasicoherence in the object classifier › forest://jonmsterling/jms-008V/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-008V.xml" title="synthetic quasicoherence in the object classifier" addr="jms-008V" type="local">synthetic quasicoherence in the object classifier</fr:link> › jms-008V/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>We consider the finitely presentable <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>-algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, i.e. the free extension of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> by an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {x}]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-008T.xml" title="synthetic quasicoherence" addr="jms-008T" type="local">synthetic quasicoherence</fr:link>, the canonical homomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}\to  V^{\operatorname {Spec}{V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}}}]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism. We will see that this homomorphism is, in fact, tracked (up to isomorphism) by the desired map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V+1\to  V^V]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  
  <html:p>First of all, the carrier of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is the coproduct <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V+1]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-008U.xml" title="spectrum of an algebra" addr="jms-008U" type="local">spectrum</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> can be seen to be <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> itself by the universal property of the free extension:</html:p>
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \operatorname {Spec}V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}} = \mathbf {hom}_{\mathrm {Alg}_{V}}{\mathopen {}\left (V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}},V\right )\mathclose {}}
    \cong  V
  ]]></fr:tex>
  
  <html:p>The canonical isomorphism above sends a homomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\operatorname {Spec}{V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}}}\xrightarrow {{f}}{V}]]></fr:tex> to the element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\mathsf {x}]]></fr:tex>. We therefore have the desired isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V+1 \cong  V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}} \cong  V^{\operatorname {Spec}{V{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathsf {x}\right  ]\mathclose {}}}}\cong  V^V]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
